19/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- German Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer will arrive in Ankara on Wednesday (21 January) at the invitation of Turkish counterpart Abdullah Gul. 
They are expected to focus on Turkey's EU membership bid, co-operation in the fight against terrorism, and other regional matters. 
Fischer also will meet with Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
In other news, Turkish police carried out a series of raids in Istanbul and seized 156.5 kg of heroin and 60 kg of hashish, according to a statement Sunday. 
That same day, border police caught 105 illegal immigrants trying to cross the border into Greece. 
All will be processed and deported. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 18/01/04)
